unittitle.value: New York Women's Culinary Alliance Archive

abstract.value: The New York Women’s Culinary Alliance, founded in 1981, fosters networking, education, and cooperation for women in the culinary and beverage fields in the New York metro area. Early founders inlcude Sara Moulton and Maria Reuge, and right from the start its members included well known authors, caterers, chefs, cooking school teachers, editors, food writers, marketers, photographers, and stylists. The Archive includes records of the organization’s founding, meeting notes, membership directories, newsletters, and reports on activities and events. There is also a video of "Moulton Visuals".

p.value: Materials are open to researchers. Please contact the Fales Library and Special Collections, fales.library@nyu.edu, 212-998-2596.
